<h2 style=3D"font-weight: normal;"><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Luxury V=
acation Packing Checklist</span></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ryhcnfSYsxWhO9iVynxyJk3KkDId=
k0lV/view?usp=3Ddrive_link" rel=3D"noopener" style=3D"font-weight: bold;">C=
lick Here For a Printable Checklist</a></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Passport (valid 6+ months) / IDs</sp=
an></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"></span><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[=
 ] Wallet (credit/debit cards, cash)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Travel insurance details<br></sp=
an></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Flight/train/hotel confirmations<br>=
</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Itinerary + emergency contacts</span=
></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Driver=E2=80=99s license / Inter=
national Driving Permit</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Vaccination card / health docume=
nts<br><br></span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Baggage Prep</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Weigh checked bag (target 50 lb =
unless your fare differs)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Measure carry-on (airline size r=
ules)<br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Liquids: 3.4 oz (100 ml) bottles, 1 =
quart bag, 1 per traveler (TSA liquids rule)<br><br></span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Clothing (adjust by trip length + laund=
ry access)<br></span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Underwear / socks</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Base layers / sleepwear</span></=
p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Tops (casual + dress</span><span=
 style=3D"color: #000000;">)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Bottoms (pants/shorts/skirts)<br=
></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Light sweater / fleece<br></span></p=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Weather layer (rain jacket / windbre=
aker)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Hat / gloves / scarf (seasonal)<=
/span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Swimwear / cover-up</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Packable down / warm layer (seas=
onal)<br><br></span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Shoes</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Comfortable walking shoes<br></s=
pan></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Dress shoes / sandals<br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Water shoes / flip-flops</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Hiking/active shoes (trip-specif=
ic)</span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Toiletries (less than 3 oz to carry on)=
</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Toothbrush / toothpaste</span></=
p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Deodorant</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Shampoo / conditioner / body was=
h<br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Razor / shaving kit</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Skincare / sunscreen</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Makeup / remover</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Hairbrush / ties</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Personal hygiene items</span></p=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Contacts / solution / glasses<br=
><br></span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Health &amp; Safety</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Personal meds + copies of prescr=
iptions</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Pain/fever reliever; motion-sick=
ness tabs</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Bandages / blister care</span></=
p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Insect repellent</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Hand sanitizer / wipes</span></p=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Water bottle</span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Electronics</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Phone + charger</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Power bank</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Headphones/earbuds</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Camera + batteries/memory cards<=
/span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Laptop/tablet + charger</span></=
p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Travel adapter / converter</span=
></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Documents (extras</span><span style=3D"=
color: #000000;">)<br></span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Copies (digital + paper) of passport=
, cards<br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Local transit passes / tickets<br></=
span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Activity confirmations / vouchers<br=
><br></span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">For Kids (if applicable)</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Favorite snacks (TSA-friendly)</=
span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Entertainment (books/activities/=
tablet)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Comfort items (stuffed animal/bl=
anket)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Diapers/wipes/cream (if needed)<=
br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Lightweight stroller / carrier</span=
></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Car seat (if required by rental)=
</span></p>
<h3><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Flight Day</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] ID/passport handy</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Liquids bag accessible</span></p=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Empty bottle to fill after secur=
ity<br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">[ ] Layered outfit (cabin temps vary)</s=
pan></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Essential meds in carry-on</span=
></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;"><br>[ ] Downloaded maps/playlists/ticket=
s</span></p>
<h2><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Using a Vacation Packing Calculator<br>=
</span></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">We love this Vacation Packing Calculator=
 from Travel Closely, which calculates everything you=E2=80=99ve added, est=
imates the weights, and shows whether you=E2=80=99re under or over your all=
owance. Handy, right? The calculator looks at all the big airlines in opera=
tion currently, from American Airlines to West Jet, British Airways to Virg=
in Australia, and there=E2=80=99s also an option to choose =E2=80=98Other=
=E2=80=99, which lets you input your weight allowance.<br><br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">It=E2=80=99s smart to set your own targe=
ts by airline and route (50 lb. checked bag limits are standard in economy,=
 but always check with your airline). The <a href=3D"https://www.transporta=
tion.gov/airconsumer/baggage-optional-fees" rel=3D"noopener"><span style=3D=
"font-weight: bold;">Department of Transportation</span></a> guides baggage=
/optional fee disclosures so you know what to expect before you book.<br><b=
r></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">The calculator is divided into adults=E2=
=80=99 and children=E2=80=99s items and includes clothes, shoes, accessorie=
s, toiletries, electronics, and entertainment, so you can quickly see how m=
uch your bag likely weighs.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Everything is calculated as averages*. W=
omen=E2=80=99s jeans weigh around 0.5 lbs, while men=E2=80=99s are typicall=
y 0.6 lbs. On the other hand, a woman's jacket weighs 1.1 lbs, while a man=
=E2=80=99s jacket weighs 1.3 lbs. So, if you pack jeans and jackets for an =
adult man and woman, your total weight would be about 3.5 pounds.</span></p=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: #000000;">Remember the <a href=3D"https://www.tsa.=
gov/travel/frequently-asked-questions/liquids-aerosols-and-gels-rule" rel=
=3D"noopener"><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;">TSA=E2=80=99s 3-1-1 liquid=
s rule</span></a> for your carry-ons! Each traveler can bring 3.4-oz contai=
ners that fit in one quart-size bag. Carry-ons are the most common thing to=
 repack at the airport.</span><span style=3D"color: #000000;"></span></p>
